value: Said to have been found at Shou-Chou, in the Huai valley.  Bought from C. T. Yoo, 1936
Bronze overlaid with silver.  Two gold figures of demons in relief on the front.  Inlaid with jade and turquoise.  The hooked end is in the form of a lion's head.

summary_title: Period of the Warring States (481-221 BC)
